            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>This collection contains microfilm copies of letters of Samuel Tilden concerning New York politics, elections, the Free Soil movement, the law for the government and organization of Texas into a territory, and the issue of slavery.</p>
                                 <p>In 1955, Norman Graebner acquired the film, made from the originals in the New York Public Library&#039;s Tilden collection. He then gave it to the Illinois Historical Survey.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


